<subSubSection pageId="243" pageNumber="848" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="243.[174,1382,1147,2639]" pageId="243" pageNumber="848">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[176,527,2412,2441]" pageId="243" pageNumber="848">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. The New Guinea Slender Rat has a wide distribution and presumably large and stable overall population, although its survival rate is low compared to other rodents (e.g. Common Lowland Mosaic-tailed Rat, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[564,839,2526,2560]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Paramelomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="243" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="platyops">Paramelomys platyops</taxonomicName>
) in its distribution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
